Ecobank’s Kenya Unit Posts 7.8% Growth in First-Half Profit on Loan Income

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-08-11T04:36:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/ecobank-s-kenya-unit-posts-7-8-growth-in-first-half-profit-on-loan-income.html
Ecobank Transnational Inc. (ETI) ’s Kenyan
unit said first-half profit climbed 7.8 percent as earnings from
loans increased.  Net income grew to 126 million shillings ($1.34 million) in
the six months through June from 117 million shilling a year
earlier, Ecobank Kenya Ltd. said in a statement published in the
Nairobi-based Daily Nation newspaper today. Net interest income,
the money banks earn from interest charges on loans, jumped 42
percent to 543.3 million shillings, it said.  Ecobank Transnational, based in Lome, Togo, operates in
more than 30 African countries.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  